rComments: Took over from a prof who taught the first term, but we got no explanation from either of them as to the reason for the switch. Boring and dry teacher. This was the course that made me stop taking French.

Considering that Napoleon tried to invade his country, Professor Medvedev is extremely gracious in maintaining a high level of passion for the language of an old enemy. It is a passion that is easily transmitted to all who happen to be within hearing range of his eloquence. Thanks to him, I am forever smitten with French culture and civilisation.
reading are very cool, difficult, challenging, but I loved them. Very tough grader. Good looking, just wanted to grab him and take him home to my mama.

He was late all the time and did not show up for 2 classes. I have to say that he is very disorganized and doesn't seem to care much about the class. However, he is the nicest, most helpful and approachable professor ever. He is eager to help and easy to talk to. Don't have to study for this class at all. Show up to class for participation marks.

He was better than Cvetanovic. Some of his class discussions were kind of pointless, but I did enjoy it when he gave us grammar reviews because I found those to be most helpful. If he just had more of a balance between the grammar and conversational component of the class, then the course would have been even more worthwile. But he's good+funny.
